 {"id":"bd-10r","title":"Implement EXISTS clause","description":"## Description

Support EXISTS subqueries in WHERE clauses.

## Python Behavior

```python
from sqlalchemy import exists, select

# Exists subquery
stmt = select(Customer).where(
    exists(
        select(Order).where(Order.customer_id == Customer.id)
    )
)

# NOT EXISTS
stmt = select(Customer).where(
    ~exists(select(Order).where(Order.customer_id == Customer.id))
)
```

## Rust Implementation

```rust
// EXISTS
let query = select!(Customer)
    .filter(exists(
        select!(Order).filter(Order::customer_id.eq(Customer::id))
    ));

// NOT EXISTS
let query = select!(Customer)
    .filter(not_exists(
        select!(Order).filter(Order::customer_id.eq(Customer::id))
    ));

// Or with method
let query = select!(Customer)
    .filter(
        select!(Order)
            .filter(Order::customer_id.eq(Customer::id))
            .exists()
    );
```

## SQL Output

```sql
SELECT * FROM customers c
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM orders o WHERE o.customer_id = c.id
)
```

