 {"id":"bd-1566","title":"Implement instance lifecycle events (before/after insert/update/delete)","description":"## Description

Add lifecycle event hooks for model instances.

## Python Behavior

```python
from sqlalchemy import event

@event.listens_for(User, 'before_insert')
def before_insert(mapper, connection, target):
    target.created_at = datetime.now()

@event.listens_for(User, 'after_update')
def after_update(mapper, connection, target):
    log_change(target)
```

## Rust Implementation

### Option 1: Trait methods
```rust
pub trait ModelEvents {
    fn before_insert(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_insert(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn before_update(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_update(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn before_delete(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_delete(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
}

#[derive(Model)]
struct User {
    created_at: Option<DateTime>,
}

impl ModelEvents for User {
    fn before_insert(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> {
        self.created_at = Some(Utc::now());
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

### Option 2: Attribute-based
```rust
#[derive(Model)]
struct User {
    #[sqlmodel(before_insert = "set_created_at")]
    created_at: Option<DateTime>,
}

impl User {
    fn set_created_at(&mut self) {
        self.created_at = Some(Utc::now());
    }
}
```

### Option 3: Closure registration
```rust
Session::on_before_insert::<User>(|user| {
    user.created_at = Some(Utc::now());
    Ok(())
});
```

## Events Needed

- before_insert / after_insert
- before_update / after_update
- before_delete / after_delete
- on_load (after loading from DB)
- on_refresh (after refresh from DB)

